Use this file in an editor with `djot-ls` attached. It is arranged so common
LSP operations have something concrete to act on.

# Document symbols

This section should appear in `textDocument/documentSymbol`.

## Nested symbol

This child heading should be nested under "Document symbols".

# Definition, hover, and references

Put the cursor on each link and try go-to-definition, hover, and find
references:

- Same-file heading: [Document symbols](#Document-symbols)
- Same-file explicit anchor: [local anchor](#local-anchor)
- Cross-file heading: [Exporter features](djot-export.dj#Exporter-features)
- Cross-file file target: [Filter playground](djot-filter.dj)
- Repeated reference: [Exporter features](djot-export.dj#Exporter-features)

{#local-anchor}
This paragraph has an explicit anchor. Rename the id `local-anchor` to update
links that point to it.

# Completion

Try these edits in insert mode:

- Start a new link label with `[` and complete `Exporter playground`.
- Complete a path inside `[target](` with `djot-filter.dj`.
- Complete an anchor after `[target](djot-export.dj#` with `Exporter-features`.
- Complete a same-file anchor after `[target](#` with `Code-actions`.

# Rename

Place the cursor on `djot-export.dj` in this link and use rename to move the
target path: [export file](djot-export.dj).

Place the cursor on `local-anchor` in either the declaration above or this link
and use rename: [local anchor](#local-anchor).

# Code actions

Open [the metadata scratchpad](metadata-scratch.dj), place the cursor at the
start of the document, and ask the editor for code actions. `djot-ls` should
offer "Add metadata".

Place the cursor on this native Djot task list item and ask the editor for code
actions. `djot-ls` should offer "Convert to task div".

- [ ] Convert this line into a task div.

After applying the action, the result should look like a list item carrying a
`created` timestamp and containing a `task` div, like this:

- {created="2026-06-20T02:39:51Z"}
  ::: task
  Convert this line into a task div.
  :::

Place the cursor inside this unfinished task div and ask for code actions.
`djot-ls` should offer "Mark task done", inserting a `done` timestamp before
the opening task fence.

::: task
Complete this task from a code action.
:::

Place the cursor inside this blocked task div and ask for code actions.
`djot-ls` should show a blocked-task hint and not offer "Mark task done" while
the dependency remains open.

{#open-dependency}
::: task
Finish the dependency first.
:::

{depends="#open-dependency"}
::: task
This task is blocked by the dependency.
:::

Place the cursor inside this recurring task div and ask for code actions.
`djot-ls` should offer "Mark task done", inserting `done`, adding an id if
needed, and appending the next task instance with `prev`.

{due="2026-06-21T17:00:00+08:00" recur="P1W"}
::: task
Review the recurring task flow.
:::

# Diagnostics

These links are intentionally broken so diagnostics have something to report:

- Missing same-file anchor: [missing](#Missing-Anchor)
- Missing file: [missing file](missing-target.dj)
- Missing cross-file anchor: [missing heading](djot-export.dj#Missing-Heading)

These duplicate anchors are intentionally broken so duplicate-anchor diagnostics
have something to report:

{#duplicate-anchor}
